#Chapter2 ## 문제1

logloss_cb<-expand.grid(depth=c(4,6,8),iterations = c(100,200),logloss=NA)

##문제2

folds <- cut(seq(1,nrow(data)),breaks=5,labels=FALSE)
for (J in 1:6){
  dataset<-data[sample(nrow(data)),]
  for (I in 1:5){
  testIndexes <- which(folds == I,arr.ind = T)
  data_train<- dataset[-testIndexes,]
  data_test<- dataset[testIndexes,]
  
  
  library(catboost)
  train_pool <- catboost.load_pool(
    data = data_train[,-'stroke'] %>% as.data.frame(),
    label = data_train[,'stroke'] %>% as.matrix(),
    cat_features = which(sapply(data[, x], is.factor))
  )
  
  
  test_pool <- catboost.load_pool(
    data = data_test[,-'stroke']%>% as.data.frame(), 
    label = data_test[,'stroke'] %>% as.matrix(), 
    cat_features = which(sapply(data[, x], is.factor))
  )
  
  start <- Sys.time()
  params <- list(
    loss_function = 'Logloss',
    depth = logloss_cb[J,1],
    iterations = logloss_cb[J,2],
    random_seed = 1234,
    train_dir = "CatBoost_output"
  )
  CatBoost <- catboost.train(learn_pool=train_pool, test_pool=test_pool, params=params)
  CatBoost_Runtime <- Sys.time() - start
  }
  test_error <- read.table("CatBoost_output/test_error.tsv", sep = "\t", header = TRUE)
  logloss_cb[J,3]<- test_error[which.min(test_error$Logloss), "Logloss"]
}

###Chapter3 ##문제1

numeric_data<-data[,c('age','avg_glucose_level','bmi')]
scaled_data<-data[,c('age','avg_glucose_level','bmi')]%>% scale() %>% as.data.table()

##문제2 두 그래프에서 보았을 때, 첫번째 그래프에서 팔꿈치처럼 꺾이는 부분이 3-4이고, 두번째 그래프에서도 4를 기점으로 떨어지고 있으므로 적절한 k는 3혹은 4인 것 같다.

require(cluster)
## Loading required package: cluster
require(factoextra)
## Loading required package: factoextra
## Welcome! Want to learn more? See two factoextra-related books at https://goo.gl/ve3WBa
s1<-fviz_nbclust(scaled_data, kmeans, method = "wss")+
  geom_vline(xintercept=NULL,linetype = 2)
s2<-fviz_nbclust(scaled_data, kmeans, method = "silhouette")

grid.arrange(s1, s2,nrow = 1)
